  "title": "Pest Control Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong><br>\nWe are seeking a dedicated and certified <strong>Pest Control Technician</strong> to join our team. The successful candidate will be responsible for implementing vector control measures to prevent and manage vector-borne diseases in various environments.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct site inspections and carry out vector surveillance.</li>\n  <li>Apply appropriate vector control methods including fogging, larviciding, and residual spraying.</li>\n  <li>Maintain records of control activities and findings.</li>\n  <li>Adhere to safety protocols and standard operating procedures.</li>\n  <li>Report any environmental issues or potential vector breeding grounds.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with team members and supervisors to ensure effective execution of control programs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Valid NEA Certified and Registered Vector Control Worker.</li>\n  <li>Workplace literacy and numeracy proficiency in reading, listening, and numeracy.</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of relevant experience in vector control.</li>\n  <li>Must be able to work in various outdoor environments.</li>\n  <li>Minimum Primary 6 education or equivalent.</li>\n</ul>",
